The paper presents new heuristics to speed up the solution convergence of Markov Decision Processes (MDPs) by prioritizing states based on their potential impacts to other states. This is a common problem in the field of artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML), which falls under the cs.AI sub-category. The paper also involves optimization techniques and algorithms, which are relevant to the cs.LG sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with the analysis of data structures and algorithms, which is relevant to the cs.DS sub-category. The paper also involves control systems and optimization, which are relevant to the cs.SY sub-category. Finally, the paper involves mathematical optimization and decision-making, which are relevant to the cs.MA sub-category.
